      "methods": [],
      "module_path": "pr",
      "docs": "Typed input for the `pr` command family. Pre-existing type (baseline: Ensure.base and WaitAndMerge.method were plain String); this track (IN-03/AC-09) changes Ensure.base and WaitAndMerge.method to Option<String> so PrDriver forwards the caller's none-means-default intent through to the composition root, which resolves merge_target / merge_method from the active track's branch_strategy_snapshot when the CLI flag is omitted -- mirroring the cli-layer EnsurePrArgs/WaitAndMergeArgs precedent already declared in cli-types.json. Role is Dto (not PrimaryAdapter): this enum is a plain input DTO consumed by PrDriver::handle, not itself the driving adapter (see R1: cli/cli_driver clap args and input DTOs use the Dto role; same role correction already applied to TrackInput in this catalogue). R9 primitive justification: base/method stay raw Option<String> because cli_driver may_depend_on=[usecase] only -- Option<domain::branch_strategy::MergeMethod> (and an equivalent branch-name value object) are architecturally impossible to name in this layer; both concepts are already modelled at the domain layer (BranchStrategySnapshot.merge_target as NonEmptyString, .merge_method as MergeMethod, both validated) and the raw-string-to-domain-type conversion happens downstream in cli_composition, which does depend on domain. The remaining fields (track_id, pr, interval, timeout, trigger_timestamp, resume) are unchanged by this track: track_id carries the same cli_driver-cannot-depend-on-domain rationale as TrackInput.track_id in this catalogue; pr/interval/timeout/trigger_timestamp/resume are opaque technical values (external PR identifier, poll timing knobs, an ISO-8601 timestamp echo, and a boolean resume flag) with no finite-value domain concept to model.",
      "spec_refs": [
        { "file": "track/items/branch-strategy-config-driven-2026-06-30/spec.json", "anchor": "IN-03" },
        { "file": "track/items/branch-strategy-config-driven-2026-06-30/spec.json", "anchor": "AC-09" }
      ],
